page.title: 17Our Day at St.Levan
page.content: On Thursday 11th of July we went to St.Levan for our last Domesday outing. We parked our things at St.Levan school and set off. The thing I remember is when we went to this house. We knocked on the door but there was no one in so we looked around the garden which was very big. We saw very big leaves which we called Giant rhubarb and we were using them as fans. We also saw a river with fish in it called Trout so we watched them for a while. We thought the garden was fascinating and a bit like a jungle . Five minutes later a lady came when we were just about to go. We asked her our questions and she answered all of them.She said"Would you like to see a watermill?".
